		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Once performed, this spell is nearly irreversible. It can be done at any time, but many necromancers choose to never take this step.</em></p><p><strong>1 Hour</strong> - Self - Permanent - Magical</p><ul><li><p>You take on an &amp;reference[undead] appearance: often skeletal, but not necessarily.</p></li><li><p>Your soul is bound to a vessel of your choosing called a soul vessel: any object that can fit within a 5 ft. cube and isn't sentient or an artifact.</p></li><li><p>The vessel is immune to nonmagical physical, &amp;reference[poison], and &amp;reference[psychic] damage.</p></li><li><p>Regardless of what it was, it now <span>has a damage threshold of 50, meaning anything that does less than 50 damage does no damage to the vessel. You must also give the vessel another weakness - a unique way of destroying it - which you must do to the item as a part of making it.</span></p></li><li><p>While the vessel is intact and functioning, you gain a limited form of immortality. If you die while within 1 mile of the vessel, your body reforms and you return to life after 24 hours next to the soul vessel (even if it later moves).</p></li><li><p>You know the location of your soul vessel, relative to you, at all times. This extends across different planes.</p></li><li><p>If you die further than 1 mile away from your soul vessel, or after your soul vessel is destroyed, you cannot be brought back from death unless a <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.bjDebvXFbxqEYkw6]{True Resurrection}</em> spell is used to revive you (as a living person) or a <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.5e0swEflzMmSszQ0]{Wish}</em> spell is used to restore you or your soul vessel.</p></li><li><p>If your soul vessel is destroyed but you survive, you are no longer able to regain hit points or spell slots from resting.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
